<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[192,1442,405,567]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,303,405,431]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Remarks.</emphasis>
This genus was transferred by 
<bibRefCitation author="Casale A." box="[655,864,405,431]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" refId="ref54848" refString="Casale A. 1988. Revisione degli Sphodrina (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Sphodrini). Monografie 5. Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali (Torino); Turin. 1024 p." type="book" year="1988">Casale (1988: 919)</bibRefCitation>
from the tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Valentine" authorityYear="1987" box="[1040,1189,405,431]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Prosphodrini">Prosphodrini</taxonomicName>
to the tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonelli" authorityYear="1810" box="[1332,1437,405,431]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Platynini">Platynini</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[194,416,438,464]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Prosphodrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[194,331,438,464]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Prosphodrus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
occur throughout the North Island although they were considered rare and thought to be cave-dwellers before their ecological requirements became better known. The species live in colonies in dense forests gullies and ravines, along rills and seepages, and hide under embedded stones during the day. They are quick to dive into nearby water when disturbed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
